# P6 Research Lab — Design Specification
### Prepared for: Bel
### Date: 2026-04-10
### Classification: Internal Reference
### Revision: 2 (split batch notebooks from interactive UI)

---

## 0. Purpose & Scope

This document specifies a **research lab** extending the existing
`WRAP_P6_BACKTEST.ipynb` / `WRAP_P6_DETECTOR_SWEEP.ipynb` pair with
experimental infrastructure for five goals:

1. **Strategy backtesting** with L3 data (fill-probability aware,
   queue-priority aware — not just bar-close signal accuracy)
2. **L1 ↔ L3 correlation** — pairing chart / L1 book features with L3
   ground-truth events
3. **L3 pattern label library** — discovery, labeling, and versioning of
   recurring L3 event shapes with forward-return distributions
4. **L1 feature training** — the feature-discovery harness that feeds
   both the correlation engine and live deployment
5. **Dual view of the order book + correlation engine** — live/replay
   synchronous L3/L2/L1 rendering and runtime pattern matching

### 0.1 Split between batch and interactive

Revision 2 splits workloads along a clear boundary:

| Workload kind | Lives where | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Long-running batch jobs (feature ranking, pattern mining, CPCV training, statistical sweeps) | Jupyter notebooks | Hours-long execution, tight iteration on code, rich pandas output |
| Interactive visualization (triple view, live correlation display) | **p6-v2 web frontend** | Replay scrubber + WebSocket + chart already exist; notebook version would be a strictly worse static copy |
| One-shot "what if" tools (virtual-order placement, pattern candidate review) | **p6-v2 web frontend** | User-driven, per-interaction, needs chart context |

The logic itself lives in a new Python package `p6lab/` that both
notebooks and the web server import. The split is about **who
consumes** the library, not where the library itself lives.

This lab's guiding principle is the **knowledge-distillation architecture**
from [OB-reference.md:698-973](./OB-reference.md): L3 is the omniscient
teacher, L1/L2 are the deployable students. Every component either labels
with L3 truth, trains on L1/L2 features, or renders the gap for review.

**Out of scope:** production live-trading wiring (Phase 6+ of the
staircase plan), P2-P5 integration, C++ reimplementation.

---

## 1. Theoretical Foundation & Citations

### 1.1 Source documents

| Document | Purpose |
|---|---|
| [OB-reference.md](./OB-reference.md) | Microstructure reference + Sector 6 distillation architecture — §1 P6 robustness (L1-43), §2 seven L3-backtestable strategies (L59-121), §3 methodology bridges (L125-151), §4 L3/L2 correlation engine (L356-549), §5 knowledge distillation (L698-973), §6 fragility index (L1537-1774), §7 stress cascade library (L1057-2240), §8 synthetic augmentation (L1336-1537), §9 walk-forward CPCV (L1778-2056) |
| [staircase-engine-plan-of-action.md](./staircase-engine-plan-of-action.md) | Phased roadmap — §1A immediate L3 strategies (L22-43), §1B backtest protocol (L44-72), §1C missing infra (L74-80), §3 trilevel phases (L187-331), §5 information-gain rule (L523) |
| [wrap-p6-backtest-spec.md](./wrap-p6-backtest-spec.md) | Existing calibration notebook spec — the batch-analytics notebook pair this lab extends |

### 1.2 Strategies the lab must enable

From [OB-reference.md:59-121](./OB-reference.md), seven L3-backtestable classes:

| # | Strategy | Deliverable |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Optimal execution | Notebook 05 + UI virtual-order tool |
| 2 | Queue priority alpha | Notebook 05 + UI virtual-order tool |
| 3 | Toxic flow avoidance | Notebook 03 (feature), notebook 06 (regime filter) |
| 4 | Spoofing-fade | Covered in WRAP_P6_BACKTEST §05 |
| 5 | Iceberg ride | Covered in WRAP_P6_BACKTEST §05 |
| 6 | Order anticipation | Notebook 04 (mining), notebook 07 (cascade) |
| 7 | Information asymmetry (VPIN) | Notebook 03 (feature), notebook 06 (regime filter) |

### 1.3 Stress cascade taxonomy

From [OB-reference.md:1175-1288](./OB-reference.md): four cascade types —
Type A Liquidity Withdrawal (slow burn), Type B Momentum Ignition
(minutes-hours), Type C Grinding Correction (multi-day), Type D
Cross-Instrument Contagion (minutes). Notebook 07 handles all four;
the UI surfaces current fragility state for Type A/B early warning.

