## 17. Build Order Recommendation

Revised to maximize parallelism between notebook work and UI work.

### Week 1 — Foundations
- `p6lab.ingestion.*`
- `p6lab.features.l1_features`
- `p6lab.features.l2_features`
- Notebook 03 `L1_FEATURE_LAB` — produces the canonical `triple_view`
  parquet that unblocks everything downstream

### Week 2 — Features + First UI Surface
- `p6lab.features.fragility_index`
- `p6lab.features.vpin`
- **UI §10.1 Triple View Panel** + `replay_api.py` triple_frame
  endpoint — can ship immediately using the parquet from notebook 03,
  even before notebooks 04-07 exist. First demoable UI work.

### Week 3 — Pattern Mining + Review Loop
- `p6lab.patterns.*`
- Notebook 04 `PATTERN_MINING`
- **UI §10.3 Pattern Review Queue** + `pattern_api.py` — ship alongside
  notebook 04 so mined candidates have an immediate review path

### Week 4 — Execution (batch + interactive)
- `p6lab.execution.*` (including `ReplayFeed` order-ID patch per §15.1)
- Notebook 05 `EXECUTION_SIM`
- **UI §10.2 Virtual Order Tool** + `fill_sim_api.py` — shares
  `p6lab.execution.fill_simulator` with notebook 05

### Week 5 — Correlation Engine
- `p6lab.correlation.*`
- `p6lab.validation.*`
- Notebook 06 `CORRELATION_LAB`
- **UI §10.4 Correlation Feed** + `correlation_api.py` — can stub
  initially with template-matcher-only; swap to trained model once
  notebook 06 exports it

### Week 6 — Cascade + Fragility
- Notebook 07 `CASCADE_LAB`
- **UI §10.5 Fragility Gauge** — initial FI_fast+FI_full display works
  with baseline weights from OB-reference; refine after notebook 07
  validates and potentially rebalances weights

### Week 7 — Close the loop
- Rerun notebook 05 with signals from the live correlation engine
  (notebook 06's output via §10.4) to measure tradeable-PnL
  improvement over raw aggregator signals
- Run all information-gain gates end-to-end
- Write notebook 03-07 + UI integration test suite

Every notebook and every UI panel is independently shippable. Partial
progress is genuinely useful — you can demo the triple view in week 2
with nothing but notebook 03's output, and keep adding surfaces without
breaking the ones already done.
